ENTRY       EC 1.1.99.39                Enzyme
NAME        D-2-hydroxyglutarate dehydrogenase;
            AtD-2HGDH
CLASS       Oxidoreductases;
            Acting on the CH-OH group of donors;
            With other acceptors
SYSNAME     (R)-2-hydroxyglutarate:acceptor 2-oxidoreductase
REACTION    (R)-2-hydroxyglutarate + acceptor = 2-oxoglutarate + reduced acceptor [RN:R10575]
ALL_REAC    R10575
SUBSTRATE   (R)-2-hydroxyglutarate [CPD:C01087];
            acceptor [CPD:C00028]
PRODUCT     2-oxoglutarate [CPD:C00026];
            reduced acceptor [CPD:C00030]
COMMENT     The enzyme, which has been characterized from the plant Arabidopsis thaliana, is highly specific for (R)-2-hydroxyglutarate. It has low activity with (R)-lactate, (R)-2-hydroxybutyrate and meso-tartrate, and no activity with the (S) isomers.
